column31: Rising temperatures and thick humid air can cause breathing difficulties for a number of people as summer approaches each year. Add a cloth face mask to the equation and those problems can worsen. Dr. Adrian DiVittorin, a pulmonologist and critical care physician states, " wearing a mask in the heat will make adults, children, athletes, and especially those already diagnosed with pulmonary or cardiac illnesses more susceptible to breathing difficulty and heat stroke." "Our body has several methods and mechanisms on how we can cool ourselves down, sweating, etc. But one of them is through breathing out hot air. So if we’re increasing our work of breathing because we’re breaking through a mask in the heat and the humidity and then were unable to exhale hot air then certainly overheating can occur.,” said Dr. DiVittorio. There are several symptoms you should watch for. “If the symptoms of heat stroke or overheating or respiratory difficulties such as severe tiredness, very fast heart rate, severe panting then absolutely take the mask off, sit down and try to cool down. Take a few breaths. If your face mask gets wet from sweating, it’s basically like having a wet towel over your face and it will make breathing even more difficult.” Dr. DiVittorio said. Whether you wear a mask or not, we want you to be safe. Please make sure you are watching out for these symptoms and taking the necessary precautions to avoid overheating. https://thevaccinereaction.org/2020/06/dangers-of-wearing-masks-in-the-heat-and-humidity/?fbclid=IwAR2gJh-j4Jy1m2IggWN3JTyTQ-3MLGz0eHPNBT5q40bJiVFFslvg5y347kQ

column31: Schisandra is a woody climbing vine that produces red spherical fruit. The whole fruit and the seed have a salty taste. The skin and pulp are sweet and sour, whereas the kernels are pungent and bitter. For this reason the Chinese name it Wuweizi (five flavours fruit) and Gomishi in Japanese. Schisandra has been used for centuries in Chinese medicine. The ancient Chinese classified the herb in many ways – as a stimulant, tonic, antiseptic, relaxant and astringent. Schisandra has also been used to treat different ailments including coughs, fatigue, impotence, memory loss and nervous complaints. It has also been acclaimed for promoting longevity and increasing physical and mental stamina. More recently, the benefits of Schisandra have been extensively studied. These studies show benefits including heart-lung function, body resistance, anticancer activities, suppression of infections in human immunodeficiency virus (HIV), and more! Check out the studies on this powerful plant!👇 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6073455/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5378736/

column31: Not all health is, or should be, "public health." In fact, the vast majority of health should be private/personal health. These days, just about everyone seems to think that all that matters is public health. We have zero discussions about what you can do, personally, to improve your health and reduce your risk of getting sick with anything -- acute or chronic. With the c-word...where are all the discussions about low vitamin D levels being correlated with more severe symptoms? Or low levels of zinc and selenium? Where are the recommendations to get your blood tested and supplement where needed? Or to get out in the sun for natural vitamin D + fresh air and exercise? Nowhere. Instead, there is a heavy -- nearly sole -- focus on what we are all supposed to do "for each other." Which leads people to reason that those who will not do those things are bad citizens, and that leads to the heavy shaming we are seeing now. Are there things we can do for each other? Sure. Let's start by teaching proper hand washing techniques. Let's change work and school policies *permanently* so that people who are sick are encouraged to STAY HOME and are able to do so. But this communal attitude has to go. This idea that we are ONLY reliant on others for our personal health is ridiculous and wrong, and it's causing serious psychological damage to the community.

column31: 📌 MASKS: WHAT DOES THE SCIENCE SAY? The idea of wearing a mask to protect others may make you feel good, like you are part of a community or a collective that cares about others. Wearing a mask may even signal virtue and goodwill. But, what if it was all based on a myth? What if wearing a mask not only offered zero protection to others, to yourself–but worse, was downright harmful to your health? Your loved ones, your children? Remember, we inhale millions of microbes every day, including viruses, bacteria and fungi–and whether you like it or not, it’s a normal part of life. Our bodies are home to trillions of microbes–THAT SERVE A PURPOSE. Which is ironically: to keep you healthy. (Being overly hygienic and sterile is associated with disease). I understand the issue. Many people are afraid of SARS-COVID-19, the one virus that took us all by surprise (but surprise, surprise COVID-19 may have been circulating for a year before we knew about it). It was found in Spain sewage waste water dated from March 2019!! That’s over a year before we knew about it. That means whatever spikes in death we saw in April 2020 were cause by OUR RESPONSE to Covid-19. It’s essentially medical error. column31: This is madness. New Jersey’s 2,500 public schools will open their doors for the 2020-2021 school year, but classes will be unlike anything students and teachers have ever experienced before, state officials announced Friday. Here are the new guidelines: --All teachers, school staff members and visitors will be required to wear masks unless they can’t for health reasons. Students must also wear masks when they can’t stay six feet apart and are "strongly encouraged", but not required, to keep their face coverings on throughout the school day. --Schools must “strive” for social distancing in the classroom and on school buses. If there is not enough room to keep students six feet apart, districts should consider physical barriers between desks and turning all desks all in the same direction. They should also consider installing barriers in buses. --Students can eat lunch in school cafeterias, but meal times must be staggered to allow for social distancing and disinfecting. Self-service and buffet-style food service will not be allowed. --Schools must set up a plan for screening students and staff for COVID-19 symptoms and work with the local health department and school nurses to use contact tracing to identify those who have come in contact with people who test positive. It will be up to districts if and how they want to test their entire staff for the coronavirus, state officials said. --Floors and sidewalks should have tape and signs to help guide how students should walk to maintain social distancing in common areas and hallways. Schools also need to step up their cleaning and disinfecting schedules. Bathrooms must be cleaned and sanitized “between use as much as possible.” --Recess and gym will be permitted, but school districts must limit the size of groups and mark off areas to “ensure separation between students.” Playground and other equipment must be disinfected between uses. Gym locker rooms will be closed. -- No indoor school sports will be allowed for the time being. Kids already have a lot to deal with in school, and now this? This will be mentally, emotionally, and physically exhausting to children. And teachers are going to have an extremely difficult job in trying to constantly enforce these new rules. How realistic is all of this really? https://www.nj.com/coronavirus/2020/06/nj-schools-will-reopen-with-masks-social-distancing-and-sweeping-new-rules-under-just-released-plan.html?fbclid=IwAR0Si8NH-uKmgIgsc5k6vv9HzITZBq9X0uaqvbhYyx-C_hkuNfJdbiqrJ6A

We're only discussing what people are supposed to do for each other. It's a great method of control. Tell the masses everything is for community benefit and we all need to do the same and feel the same. Social shaming and herd mentality will get most to comply. Complete psychological manipulation. There was an experiment done once with two dogs. Dog A was placed in a cage and his food bowl was hooked up to an electric shock, so that every time he tried to eat he'd get shocked. Dog B was in a cage right next to him, but could not see him, and received a shock every time Dog A ate. Dog A quickly figured out he would get shocked when he ate, so he minimized eating and lost some weight, but otherwise did okay. Dog B, though, grew extremely depressed and did poorly because the shocks were seemingly random. The Dog that felt in control of the situation, however difficult, did much better than the dog who felt completely out of control. That is what they are doing to you right now. They are teaching you that you are not, cannot be in control of your own life. That you're at the mercy of others. They are priming you with fear and uncertainty so you will lash out at others and shame them into compliance. column36:
The California Medical Board opened six more cases against me a couple years ago, and I am happy to announce that these cases have been settled. The board offered me a settlement of two additional years of probation in lieu of going to trial, and I accepted their offer. They also agreed to lift restrictions on doing house calls (most Docs on probation aren’t allowed to do home visits). 

As you know, I am currently already on probation for writing a court opinion letter in 2015 (nothing to do with vaccine medical exemptions) advising that a child should not resume vaccines due to a severe neurological reaction during infancy. The judge in that custody battle upheld my medical opinion, and did not force the child to resume vaccines, but the medical board disagreed. That probationary period has another year left. This new settlement will extend this for another two years beyond that. 

These six new cases involved the issue of vaccine medical exemptions (whereas my first case did not). Here are the deets in case you are curious:

— I granted vaccine exemptions to two siblings because one of them has a severe medical condition that research has shown can get worse with ongoing vaccination. The other child doesn’t have the condition, yet, but dad does. Exemption for reasons in a family’s medical history was a right guaranteed under California law at that time (SB277).

— I gave an exemption to a child with a family member who had a severe permanent neurological injury after vaccines. Again, family history of reactions was specifically amended into SB 277 in order to get that law passed in 2015. This family was a perfect example of why they wrote SB 277. 

— I exempted a teen who had a severe reaction to an infant vaccine. Her own doctor told her to opt out of that vaccine after that, and I agreed she should be exempt from the teen booster dose.

— And finally, I saw two siblings who I did NOT give exemptions to. One parent reported me to the board as part of their custody battle. 

Why would I settle for more probation when all these exemptions (and non-exemptions) were completely in line with existing California law at that time (SB 277)? It’s simple. Even if I had won my case in court before the administrative judge, which I had a decent chance of doing so, the medical board still gets to decide my punishment — even if I win. Since the medical board already determined that my exemptions were wrongly granted (thus the reason for their accusation against me), they would have likely punished me with more probation and other penalties if I’d gone to court. Remember, this is the medical board that helped get SB 276/714 passed, which eliminated family medical history as a reason for exemption starting in 2020. I was advised to save the couple more years of legal anguish and large amount of money and settle the cases. And since no one can write exemptions anymore (except in cases of severe brain injury or near-death allergic reactions), I wouldn’t be fighting for the right to continue supporting families by evaluating their need for one. 

There could absolutely be value in fighting this fight against the board, as I see two other doctors doing. I applaud them and hope and pray they win. We know we are in the right. It would be great to get some legal wins on the books. 

If you would like to support my ongoing efforts in fighting to improve vaccine safety and protect informed consent, listen to and share my two podcasts with everyone you know: “The Vaccine Conversation with Melissa and Dr. Bob” and “A Tale of Two Sides” (search these titles on any podcast app or on google). Follow me on www.ImmunityEducationGroup.org:=:https://immunityeducationgroup.org/ and the IEG Facebook page. The world is waking up to the truth, and the truth will prevail.

column36:
This is my speech on June 23rd, 2020 from the front steps of the California State Capital in Sacramento, CA.  I will never stop speaking the truth to anyone who will listen and I will never stop fighting for our God-given freedoms. I was never in their plan and I’m thankful to be an unexpected ripple of change in the tsunami that will crumble the entire corrupt system. 

Just remember, you cannot take the truth and be mad at who tells it to you....I’m just the messenger.

“My name is Erin Olszewski and I flew in from Tampa, Florida, to speak on our fight for freedom – a battle that brave Americans have been waging since 1776, and never more so than today.  I am a firm believer in people over profit and facts over fear.  

There are a lot of people here. I see some old faces and I see some new faces. If you’re new, welcome to the right side of history!  It’s inspiring to look and see so many of you standing up for our freedom of speech, our freedom to protest…and our freedom to decide whether we want to wrap a useless piece of fabric around our faces and accept this as the “new normal.”  To me, there’s nothing normal about this. I’m not sure where in the Constitution it says that our governors have the power to mandate that, but I doubt they’ve read the Constitution lately anyways.

I’m here to bring you the facts and let you know how the American people have been lied to.  I was at the epicenter of the epicenter, Elmhurst hospital in NYC, where all these bad actor legislators are basing all their draconian, unconstitutional rules and suggested “mandates” from.  I’m going to explain why it’s all a lie.  Bear with me, the details I share with you are important. 

Freedom isn’t just a buzz word to me. I have put my life on the line to protect it many times throughout the years. 

First, when I was 17, I joined the Army before I even graduated high school, and served in Operation Iraqi Freedom. 

I will never forget the courage, dedication, and bravery of the men and women I served alongside in Iraq. But I also will never forget how the U.S. government treated us: Like we didn’t deserve to have a voice. Like we were dispensable. Like we were just another brick in the wall.

When I returned home to the States, I began a career in nursing.  I thought that completing my military service meant that the government was no longer controlling my life. But boy was I wrong. 

In nursing school, I was essentially brainwashed with the mainstream medical message of immunizations. Vaccines are good, they told me. Vaccines save lives, they told me. I was young and naïve, but I’m embarrassed to say today that I swallowed  the vaccine mythology hook, line, and sinker. That would be the last time I would ever accept the government’s lies so single-mindedly. 

It took a personal tragedy to wake me up. My son Drew was 12 months old when he went for a round of immunizations. This “well visit” would change all of our lives forever. He went from being a smiling, bubbly, talkative little boy to a ghost. He stopped talking. He stopped making eye contact. The little boy that I knew was gone, and along with it, everything I ever thought I knew about vaccines. 

As I learned more, I learned what had happened to Drew was happening to children all around the country. I learned how to heal Drew, and it became my mission  to protect children and parents  from unnecessary vaccine injury.  

While I continued that fight, I learned that another dangerous enemy was barreling towards us: Coronavirus, COVID-19, The Wuhan flu, . Whatever you call it.  This pandemic, and the overreaction to it, is the biggest threat to America, our values, and our Constitution that many of us have never faced in our lifetimes. And it’s NOT because this disease by itself is so deadly. I know this because I have seen it firsthand.

At my hospital in Florida, we saw just a few coronavirus patients. They came in, we treated them, and they left to return to their families. The one man that we actually admitted had a preexisting condition, but he ended up being fine. 

Back in April, as New York was at the height of its outbreak, I volunteered to go to the frontlines as a travel nurse. Not too many people were volunteering to go INSIDE the hospitals in NYC - the epicenter of corona deaths in the US, but my background made me an ideal candidate for this mission. Once There, I was placed at Elmhurst Hospital: The epicenter of the epicenter. 

Before I even got there, Elmhurst had become notorious for “apocalyptic” conditions. They didn’t have enough ventilators. They didn’t have enough nurses. They didn’t have enough PPE. But that wasn’t why patients were dying. Patients were dying because the hospitals seemed to be more concerned about making money than treating the patients. 

I knew from the very first day I stepped foot in that hospital, something was seriously wrong.  Trash bins were overflowing. (truncated)

column31: 2015 Study: "A cluster randomised trial of cloth masks compared with medical masks in healthcare workers“ Objective: The aim of this study was to compare the efficacy of cloth masks to medical masks in hospital healthcare workers (HCWs). The null hypothesis is that there is no difference between medical masks and cloth masks. Results: The rates of all infection outcomes were highest in the cloth mask arm, with the rate of ILI (iInfluenza-like illness) statistically significantly higher in the cloth mask arm (relative risk (RR)=13.00, 95% CI 1.69 to 100.07) compared with the medical mask arm. Cloth masks also had significantly higher rates of ILI compared with the control arm. An analysis by mask use showed ILI (RR=6.64, 95% CI 1.45 to 28.65) and laboratory-confirmed virus (RR=1.72, 95% CI 1.01 to 2.94) were significantly higher in the cloth masks group compared with the medical masks group. Penetration of cloth masks by particles was almost 97% and medical masks 44%. Conclusions: This study is the first RCT of cloth masks, and the results caution against the use of cloth masks. This is an important finding to inform occupational health and safety. Moisture retention, reuse of cloth masks and poor filtration may result in increased risk of infection. Further research is needed to inform the widespread use of cloth masks globally. However, as a precautionary measure, cloth masks should not be recommended for HCWs, particularly in high-risk situations, and guidelines need to be updated. column31: People are concerned about how much influence the Gates foundation has over the W.H.O. and rightfully so. If the United States government withdraws from the World Health Organization, the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation is poised to become the agency’s top donor. The potential of this change is raising questions about what such influence from a single private foundation could mean. WHO’s list of top 20 donors for the two-year budget cycle of 2018 and 2019 reveals that the U.S. provided the agency with $893 million, accounting for 20% of WHO’s budget, whereas the Gates foundation contributed $531 million, or 12% of WHO’s budget. Lawrence Gostin, director of WHO’s Collaborating Center on National and Global Health Law stated that, “If a private foundation were to become WHO’s highest donor, it would be transformational. It would enable a single rich philanthropist to set the global health agenda." How do you feel about the Gates' influence on the W.H.O.? https://www.devex.com/news/big-concerns-over-gates-foundation-s-potential-to-become-largest-who-donor-97377

column35: Ashley
column36:
Chronic illness, infections, and toxicity.

When we treat the body with natural “medicine” (nutrient-dense diet, antioxidants, bioflavonoids, herbs, vitamins, minerals, fresh air, sunlight, exercise, restful sleep, meditation, healthy relationships, clay, etc.) we are supporting the immune system and improving its function. 

Through going this route, we are not only reducing the intake of harmful, toxic material, but we are increasing the capability and efficiency of our detoxification mechanisms. We are helping the body work the way it is intended to work. 

On the other hand, when we attempt to manage or prevent symptoms with pharmaceutical drugs, antibiotics, and vaccines, we are attempting to “trick” or thwart natural biological and physiological processes, typically by shutting down the immune system’s warning signs. 

🚫 Inflammation. Pain. Frequent infections...

These are all warning signs. 

Signs that the immune system is working to try to remove damaged/toxic cells. 

💡 “Autoimmunity”? Is your immune system confused? 

❌ No.

Your immune system is intelligently going after cells that are losing function due to increased intracellular toxicity.

Yes, this causes inflammation. 
Inflammation causes pain. 

If your lymphatic system, kidneys, or skin are unable to remove toxicity and cellular waste from the body, you will develop a chronic condition.

💊 Pharmaceutical drugs may alleviate symptoms temporarily (obstructing the immune system from attempting to go after damaged cells) but will ultimately serve to accelerate organ/tissue degeneration and failure.

———————————————

🧫  What about bacterial infections? 

Pathogenic bacteria grows... where cells are toxic. 

The more toxic metals you are exposed to, the more your gut microbiome is negatively impacted. You lose beneficial gut microbes as harmful strains gain a stronger foothold. 

E. coli, Salmonella, Enterobacter, H. pylori, Legionella pneumophila...

An overgrowth of these can lead to a variety of acute and chronic infections.

Eczema, food intolerances, inflammatory bowel disease, pneumonia, sepsis... 

💊 Antibiotics may temporarily kill bad bacteria... while also killing off good bacteria. In turn, this makes your microbiome even more susceptible to the overgrowth of harmful bacteria/microbes in the future if you do not reduce your toxic body burden and promote an internal environment that welcomes beneficial microbes. 

This is another reason why avoiding toxic exposures and improving the strength of your detoxification processes is so vital. 

———————————————

🦠 What about viral infections? 

It is already known that vitamin C, NAC (N-acetyl cysteine - precursor to glutathione which is our major detoxifying antioxidant), zinc, vitamin A & D, and many other natural substances, improve our immune system defenses against viruses.

Why is this? What is it about having a strong immune system that is protective against viral infection? 

👉🏻 Reduced toxic body burden via improved detoxification.

Like moths to a flame and mosquitoes to stagnant water, viruses are “drawn” to a toxic internal environment. 

When the body is fighting a viral infection, you may experience a range of negative symptoms: Fatigue, body aches, mucus production and sinus congestion, fever, and oftentimes a rash.

When a person decides to do a juice fast or suddenly eat very clean, healthy food, one of the first things that may happen is they experience flu-like symptoms. Fatigue, body aches, mucus production and sinus congestion, and even fever or rash. 

Or think about if you’re exposed to a high level of smoke or particulate air pollution. What happens? You cough! Your lungs begin to attempt to expel the harmful material you breathed into your lungs. Depending on the length of the exposure, you may be coughing up mucus for several days. 

Here we have the same set of unpleasant symptoms being experienced, yet in the first example, these symptoms are viewed as negative. In the next two examples, these symptoms are acknowledged as a GOOD - they are a sign that the immune system is working to purge the toxic waste that has accumulated in the body. 

The evidence shows that the more febrile infectious diseases you have as a child (infections that come with a fever), the lower your risk of cancer. column31: Tips to stay healthy ☺️ #1: Stay home if you're sick! Seriously, just stay home. Especially don't go to parties, playgrounds and other "fun" places. #2: Wash your hands! Scrub for 30 seconds using warm water. Do this before and after going out places, after the bathroom, before and after eating. #3: Limit sugar consumption. No more than 25g per day and some days none. Watch for hidden sugar in condiments and drinks. Sugar depresses your immune system in many ways, creating inflammation and vitamin and mineral deficiencies. #4: Focus on real foods. Fruits, veggies, meats, whole grains. Rich in vitamins, minerals, antioxidants, and more, these foods support your immune system. Avoid or minimize processed options. #5: Drink fresh water. Tap water contains chlorine, fluoride, pharmaceuticals, farm run off, and other junk. Filter your water and drink plenty of it. Minimize or eliminate sugary drinks. #6: Move your body. Walk, run, play sports, whatever works. Your lymphatic system gathers up waste from your cells throughout your body and needs to move to be eliminated. Since the lymphatic system doesn't have a pump, movement is the only way to get rid of it. Sluggish or clogged lymph can make you sick due to the build up of waste. #7: Reduce stress Chronic stress means high cortisol levels, which creates inflammation and lowers immunity. Practice deep breathing, write in a journal, insist on balance. #8: Include key supplements This will look different for each person. Herbs can provide extra vitamins and minerals, antioxidants, improve the stress response, support the immune system, and more. Deficiencies in vitamin D, C, zinc and selenium in particular are responsible for more frequent illness and greater severity of symptoms. Take care of yourself. Be responsible to your community. But first, take care of your own body. Each of us has the responsibility for our own health. There are no shortcuts -- no pills, no magic potions -- that can make up for unhealthy behaviors in the long run. Expecting others to get vaccines or wear masks or take personal risks with their health for you also will not work and is not fair. Health matters. Protect yours.

column31: Friends, are you prepared for the 4th of July firework {season} to keep your pet calm and safe? 🇺🇸 🐾🐾🍉🐕 Any effort you can implement now to minimize feelings of anxiety, stress, panic and fear is time well spent. Sadly, this is the holiday that is the busiest for shelters across the country as many dogs run away during the fireworks shows. When the bombs and cannons start going off, dogs do not understand and instantly go into a fight or flight mode. Many will jump through windows and doors and injure themselves or even die, trying to get away from the fireworks. July 4th is the worst day of the year for most dogs and their people, however, being prepared ahead of time can lessen stress for both of you 🌻 Here is my article with 13 great tips, here is a sneak peak .. 1. Exercise Your Dog Before the Fireworks Start! A tired dog is a calm dog. 2. Stay Home. Offering them safety and comfort and supervision will greatly help keep them calm and sage. 3. Keep Calm. The owner’s frame of mind is very influential to dogs, and it’s been shown that anxious dog owners are more prone to have dogs that develop noise phobia and other anxieties. Your dog will respond and react to your nonverbal cues. If you are nervous, uncomfortable, irritated or tense when you hear fireworks your dog will sense that and respond accordingly. 4. Drown Out the Sound. I've created a “bunker” for Tuck, my German Shepherd in our basement. It has a very large kennel with nice thick soft blankets and I have a radio on and a nice fan. 5. Essential Oils to the Rescue. Aromatherapy works very well for animals, I use 3-4 drops of lavender, stress away and/or peace and calming along his spine, he relaxes unbelievably within 5 minutes. 6. CBD oil can be amazing to support their ECS. Supporting the ECS helps with balancing the autonomic nervous system, the fight or flight components and keeping your dog calm and having restful deep sleep. 7. Real Food Nutrition. Your dogs nervous system, neurology and brain function is dependent on the quality of nutrients you are feeding him/her. Their ancestral diet of real food such as beef, liver, eggs, sardines and a small amount of greens will help to rebuild, repair and boost their immunity, in turn helping them stay balanced in regards to their autonomic nervous system, the flight or flight. 8. Respect Your Dog’s Fear. Allow your dog to hide if he/she feels more comfortable in its crate or under a bed. 9. Provide a Distraction. Break out your dog’s favorite healthy treats, play a game, or give it some extra cuddle time, this can really help reassure you pet that everything will be okay an that they are safe. 10. Consider Boarding. If you are going to be out for the day/night and your dog has a daycare he just loves, consider leaving him/her there with other dog buddies and a staff to keep an eye on him/her. Plus, many day cares are so well-insulated, and there is so much noise from other dogs barking, that your dog may not even hear the fireworks on the big night. 11. Try a Thunder Shirt. There are many different brands on the market including the Thunder Shirt and the Anxiety Wrap, which were tested by Tufts University and is approved by them to diminish signs of fear in dogs during thunderstorms. 12. If Absolutely Necessary, Don't Rule out Calming Medication. I'm not one for medication unless absolutely necessary due to the side effects, but in this case, however, if your dog really freaks out you can ask your vet for a mild sedative, but try the other things before medicating your dog. 13. Be Prepared. All these tips will help you to provide safety and comfort to your best friend ..ahead of time to offer you and them the best weekend possible. What do you have planned for the 4th of July weekend? 🇺🇸 🐾🐾💥🍉☀️🐕🎉🎊 Full article with more helpful solutions ✨➜ http://www.integrativenutritionaltherapies.com/nervous-system-calming-tips-for-your-dog/

column31: A lot of people are upset about the new C-word update to their phones. You may see something in your phone settings such as "COVID-19 exposure notifications" or "COVID-19 exposure Logging". This is an application programming interface (API) that will enable exposure notifications. It's not an app; it's the framework within the operating system that will allow such an app to function once it becomes available and if you decide to install it. However, people are rightly concerned about privacy risks from apps that track their activities given that such exposure can result in significant risks! The actual app will work somewhat like this - When someone downloads the app, short-range Bluetooth signals known as “chirps” are emitted from the smartphone and picked up by other nearby phones also running the app. If that person later tests positive, they can upload their chirps from recent weeks to a public database. Others with the app would then be notified when their phones picked up infected individuals’ chirps — alerting them that they may have been exposed. If that occurs, they’ll receive information from public health officials regarding an appropriate course of action, which may include symptom checks, seeking testing or self-quarantining. Find out more here 👇 https://www.discovermagazine.com/health/how-will-covid-19-contact-tracing-apps-work-in-the-u-s Is this even necessary? Would you download the app? What are your thoughts? https://www.forbes.com/sites/daveywinder/2020/06/20/have-apple-and-google-suddenly-uploaded-a-covid-19-tracking-app-to-your-phone-android-iphone-exposure-notification-contact-tracing/#2f8153060545

column31: During lockdown, vaccination rates fell...and so did infant mortality. A new study looks at all-cause mortality during the shutdowns due to the C-word, and noticed something quite interesting: infant mortality FELL by 30% during these months compared to the last 6 years. Why was infant mortality down so sharply? There are several possibilities: *Infants were staying home and were not being exposed to illnesses in daycare and other public spaces *Infants were more likely to be breastfed because mothers were home with them *Vaccine schedules were disrupted, and fewer infants were getting their vaccines "on time" That last one is the one we need to talk about, because it's likely the most striking change that we saw. So far we only have a correlation between lower vaccination rates and sharply lower infant mortality. But given how much and how quickly that changed...shouldn't we follow up on this and ask if it's causal? And if it IS causal...shouldn't we re-examine our infant vaccine schedule? This is too important to ignore. Hundreds of babies per year could be saved. Read the full paper here --> https://www.cohealthchoice.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Lessons-from-the-Lockdown-vF-6-17-20.pdf?fbclid=IwAR2gtFkKdsG-RdWnoRw08jJ5mw7HR4tUojWRoBF3feuUfnM3J2kMxCgV0yg

column36:
Pathologists will tell you that it is incredibly rare that any chief medical examiner change a cause of death. 

Evee's "undetermined" cause of death came March 28th, 2019. My (true) story is that I sought out a second opinion by a Dr. Douglas Miller, neuropathologist with the University of Missouri. He had Evee's tissue slides, autopsy and autopsy photos, and the story. Chief medical examiner, Dr. Quinn Strobl, sent slides but never sent the most important part of Evee's brain, the medulla. Dr. Miller found a cellular infiltration in Evee's hippocampus and when I asked the office to do a CD68 immunostain on that tissue to confirm the infiltration of histiocytes and when I asked her if she had saved my daughter's medulla (Monday, June 24th), she took two days and she sent me "the letter". Read all the proofs that have been dismissed by "others" including national news outlets here: https://www.justiceforevee.org/post/the-timeline-of-corruption

I received that letter and I lost it. I was bawling. I couldn't believe what I had just read, what I was experiencing. I knew this woman was bad at her job and pro-v, but I didn't know the level of evil I was really dealing with. So I made a phone call to my neuropathologist consultant, which I legally recorded.

Here is that phone call:  https://youtu.be/iEkTekwLC0A:=:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iEkTekwLC0A&feature=youtu.be

NBC then, with the help of the medical examiner's office, wrote this article to try and discredit my story because it's a powerful one, and full of truth. 

NBC Article Quotations:

𝙌𝙪𝙤𝙩𝙚: "The medical examiner initially found the cause of death to be "undetermined," with co-sleeping with an adult as a "significant condition." Three months later, at Clobes' request, the same examiner reviewed the case and amended the cause of death to positional asphyxia, or suffocation."

𝙇𝙞𝙚: I NEVER asked Dr. Quinn Strobl to review my case. Again, I had a private neuropathologist working the case and when we asked for more tissue and an immunostain confirmation, she took it upon herself to (not review anything) and punitively change the cause of death.

𝙇𝙞𝙚: Although this cause of death is not Evee's cause of death. Positional asphyxia is also not the same as suffocation. It's simply a "risk factor" for "SIDS" as Dr. Miller explains in the phone call. "Mechanical asphyxia" and "accidental suffocation" are 'more' alike, still not though. 

𝙌𝙪𝙤𝙩𝙚: "a study of tissue samples retained by Wright County"

𝙇𝙞𝙚:  The tissues are retained by Anoka County, this just shows how much of a shitty journalist she is.

𝙌𝙪𝙤𝙩𝙚:  Miller said his investigation found no evidence that vaccines had contributed to Evee's death. He said he told Clobes of his conclusion, and had declined to support her case in the federal government's National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program, known more commonly as Vaccine Court. He declined to name the factors that led to his decision, citing concern for Clobes' privacy.

Online, however, Clobes claimed Dr. Miller's report offered "proof" that Evee had suffered "a cellular infiltration triggered by an immune response from the vaccinations."

In an email to NBC News, Miller said the neuropathologist Clobes referred to "was not me, if he or she actually exists."

"I did not tell Ms. Clobes of any such finding," Miller said, "and I did not provide her or her attorney with any report which alleged any such finding."

𝙇𝙞𝙚:  We have confirmed proof in writing that Dr. Miller made no such statements and never gave NBC permission to quote him, nor did they follow up to confirm any of his quotations. If you listen to the phone call, I mention the CD68 stain (a confirmation test meaning he did find a cellular infiltration) and at the end of the call I briefly say "not to mention you found something". The phone call gets across Dr. Miller's opinion of what Dr. Quinn Strobl did, he is stunned. Dr. Miller did not provide a report but did provide an email of the summary of his report to me. We were cut off from any further tissue or help from the office, how would he be able to do any further testing? Other experts have since been retained to do Evee's testing (I had to hire a lawyer and we were able to get the actual formalin-fixed, wet tissue out of the office last winter) as the NBC article has turned Dr. Miller off and unfortunately the NVICP special masters have denied his theory in court, and he is no longer an expert for families pursuing the v compensation program.

𝙌𝙪𝙤𝙩𝙚:  According to reports by a detective who examined Evee at the scene and the medical examiner who performed Evee's autopsy, the skin on Evee's face had creases that looked like they could have come from a blanket. Areas of her nose, chest, arms and legs were discolored and pooled with blood, indicating Evee had been face-down for some time.

column31: Did masks prevent the spread of the 1918 Spanish Influenza? Experts examined the evidence and concluded masks failed to control infection. Given that we know from autopsies that "The majority of deaths in the 1918–1919 influenza pandemic likely resulted directly from secondary bacterial pneumonia caused by common upper respiratory–tract bacteria.” And given that the majority of deaths were in healthy young adults, age 20-40 years old—Did mask wearing actually increase mortality? "In December 1918, the American Public Health Association recommended that the “wearing of proper masks” should be compulsory for medical staff, occupations such as “barbers, dentists, etc.,” and “all who are directly exposed to infection.” However, they found that “as to beneficial results consequent on the enforced wearing of masks by the entire population at all times was contradictory,” and thus DID NOT recommend “the widespread adoption of this practice.” In 1919, Wilfred Kellogg’s study for the California State Board of Health concluded that mask ordinances “applied forcibly to entire communities” did not decrease cases and deaths, as confirmed by comparisons of cities with widely divergent policies on masking. In a 1921 study, Warren T. Vaughn declared “the efficacy of face masks is still open to question.” The problem was human behavior: Masks were used until they were filthy, worn in ways that offered little or no protection. Vaughn’s sobering conclusion: “It is safe to say that the face mask as used was a failure.” In 1927, Edwin Jordan’s definitive study (JAMA) as a series of articles and then book, determined that masks were effective when worn by patients already sick or by those directly exposed to victims, including nurses and physicians.” But for others “The effect of mask wearing throughout the general community is not easy to determine.” (Via healthaffairs.org) Let’s not forget that at this time they thought influenza was a bacteria, hundreds of times larger than viruses. And they were vaccinating people against “influenza” the bacteria. #scienceisunsettling #covid #spanishflu #spanishinfluenza #coronavirus #masks Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2599911/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1362453/ https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/011933637 https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001583712 https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/article-abstract/251741 https://quod.lib.umich.edu/f/flu/8580flu.0016.858

column35: MyKore Essentials
column36:
Scientists use nanotechnology to show that Vitamin D signals nitric oxide to repair blood vessels

In a recent study published in the International Journal of Nanomedicine researchers used nanotechnology to study the real time effects of vitamin D3 on the lining of blood vessels.

Although we typically think of vitamin D3 relating to the health of bones, a correlation between vitamin D3 levels and cardiovascular health has been observed in many recent studies.

Scientists at Ohio University used nanosensors to examine the effects of vitamin D3 on single endothelial cells which line the arteries. The nanosensors have diameters about 1,000 times smaller than a human hair.
They discovered that vitamin D3 significantly stimulates nitric oxide, which is a signaling molecule in the regulation of blood flow and clot formation.
Vitamin D3 was also associated with lower cardiovascular system oxidative stress.

This effect of vitamin D3 may prove to be beneficial in the support of healthy blood pressure and other conditions related to the heart and circulatory system.

International Journal of Nanomedicine 2018:13 455–466

https://www.dovepress.com/nanomedical-studies-of-the-restoration-of-nitric-oxideperoxynitrite-ba-peer-reviewed-fulltext-article-IJN

column31: Not only is chicken pox NOT a big deal in children, it actually has benefits! In one of the largest studies to date, an international consortium led by researchers in the Dan L Duncan Comprehensive Cancer Center at Baylor College of Medicine reported an inverse relationship between a history of chicken pox and glioma, a type of brain cancer, meaning that children who have had the chicken pox may be less likely to develop brain cancer. In the study, the team reviewed information from the Glioma International Case-Control Study is a large, multi-site consortium with data on 4533 cases and 4171 controls collected across five countries. They found a 21 percent reduced risk of developing glioma with a positive history of chicken pox. Furthermore, they identified the protective effective was greater in higher grade gliomas. The large study validates earlier studies showing this link, Bondy said. “It provides more of an indication that there is some protective benefit from having the chicken pox,” she said. “The link is unlikely to be coincidental.” https://www.bcm.edu/news/chicken-pox-may-reduce-risk-brain-cancer#:~:text=In%20one%20of%20the%20largest,had%20the%20chicken%20pox%20may

column31: In 1860, Florence Nightingale wrote “It it is the unqualified result of all my experience with the sick, that second only to their need of fresh air is their need of light. That, after a closed room, what hurts the most is a dark room. And that it is not only light, but direct sunlight they want.” ☀️ She also noted that almost all the patients in the hospital slept facing the window, seeking out light “exactly as plants always make their way to the light” even when lying on that side of their body was uncomfortable or painful to them. In 1929, medical writer Victor Dane published “The Sunlight Cure.” He concluded with this bold statement: “If you wish to obtain a general idea of the powers of the sun, and to know the names of the various diseases it benefits, buy a medical dictionary and memorize the names of all the diseases you find therein. The sun is the great healer of healers, truly an elixir vitae.” Today, we know that the sun’s powerful healing rays: ☀️ kill bacteria ☀️ deliver vitamin D ☀️ trigger melanin production & endorphin release ☀️ support immune health ☀️sync our circadian rhythm Plus it just feels FANTASTIC to catch those rays! 💫 This is why I spend as much time outdoors as possible & I commit to catching the sunrise every. single. morning. 🌞 Listen to Wise Traditions podcast #200 “Top 5 Health Hacks” 🎧 for the scoop on when I started this habit & why I love it & recommend it so much. 🧡 (Yes, I was the guest on this episode!) If I seem slightly obsessed with the sun & its healing powers, well...yes, admittedly I am. 😁 Any questions? P.S. It pollutes fluoride into the atmosphere and back in the 1940s, the 1950s when fluoridation was being introduced, there were a lot of lawsuits because fluoride air pollution was harming cattle, vegetation and human health around these factories. The polluters hired scientists to defend them in court against these lawsuits and that’s the foundation of the science that says fluoride is safe in the small amount that’s added to water because it was very similar to the amount people were being exposed to in the air. column31: There were more than 1 million black-owned businesses in the U.S. at the beginning of February. By mid-April, 440,000 black business owners had shuttered their company for good — a 41% plunge. By comparison, 17% of white-owned businesses closed during the same period. Several factors explain the high rate of closures of black-owned businesses. Many lack access to bank credit, making it harder to survive financial emergencies. Many are micro-enterprises, providing a livelihood to a sole proprietor or a few employees at most. Profit margins are thin, while owners' financial savings are often meager, making them vulnerable to sudden downturns. Surveys show that the vast majority of black business owners who applied for emergency relief after the virus struck through the Paycheck Protection Program were denied a loan. The demise of so many black-owned businesses this year also highlights the legacy of racism in America. Black owners have historically been denied loans more than any other racial group, according to Federal Reserve data. As a result, many African-Americans with a business avoid banks altogether. UC Santa Cruz professor Robert Fairlie said many black owners will face considerable obstacles resurrecting their business after the pandemic eases, citing the huge wealth gap between black and white Americans. Many African-American households lack the financial resources required to rebuild, such as bank savings, access to a home equity line of credit, or the ability to borrow from family and friends, he explained. We do understand that this is affecting business owners of all races. But it is important to discuss the hurdles that black business owners face. If we want change, we must bring these issues to light. https://www.cbsnews.com/news/black-owned-busineses-close-thousands-coronavirus-pandemic/

column31: This is why we're so passionate about magnesium lotion (Good Night Lotion). A message from our founder and herbalist: When I was pregnant with my second and third babies, there were a couple of...not fun things that happened. First, I didn't sleep well. It didn't help that we had no a/c and they were both summer babies, of course. But I found it difficult to fall asleep and sleep soundly. Chiro helped, but I couldn't go daily or anything. The other thing was, once in each pregnancy, I had a blood sugar issue. I drank a very sugary drink on an empty stomach, and it spiked my levels so high I fainted. (No one noticed the first time because I was sitting in the passenger seat of the car, alone. The second happened at the mall so everyone knew. The first time, we went to L&D to check on things and since it was 2009, they shrugged and said "probably swine flu" even though I had NO symptoms of it. The second time, the EMTs came and tested my sugar, which was like 270...ridiculously high. But I was okay and decided not to go in, and talked to my midwives instead that night.) The underlying reason for both of these things, though, was the same...low magnesium levels! When I was pregnant with my fourth, I started reading about magnesium and how important it was. I decided to try it to help with sleep. The spray was so itchy and uncomfortable, I sat and counted the minutes until I could wipe it off. I thought, there has to be a better way. So I created my first magnesium lotion. And it WORKED. I slept well, wasn't itchy or uncomfortable, and -- no more blood sugar issues! (That was just a fun bonus.) I've used it in every pregnancy since, and, well, all the time. (Checked my sugar in my sixth pregnancy an hour or so after eating -- 80. Perfectly normal.) I LOVE magnesium lotion. I use it every night. And when I don't, I notice. I'll be tired, but feel restless and unable to fall asleep. I get up to get the lotion...and fall asleep easily shortly after! It has worked on the kids, too, when they have growing pains or can't fall asleep at night, or wake up at 3 am and can't get back to sleep. Generally, it's awesome stuff. Do you use it...or feel like it would benefit you?

column31: According to a June study from an economic research organization, the C-virus pandemic has led to the largest drop in small business ownership in the United States, affecting black business owners the most. 3.3 million business owners are not actively working. Of the 3.3 million, 1.1 million small business owners were black, according to the study. Black business owners shrank from 1.1 million to 640,000 — a 41% difference. Latino business owners represented the second-largest loss at 32% from February to March, the study showed. Asian business owners were at 26%, and 17% white business owners, the study continued. More than 100,000 businesses permanently closed by mid-May, a study found, according to The Washington Post. The Small Business Administration ran out of funds for the Paycheck Protection Program on April 16. Secretary of the Treasury Steven Mnuchin said he hopes the Paycheck Protection Program will ensure businesses’ continued operations. The losses from small business owners due to coronavirus were four times the losses of the Great Recession, according to Axios. You can find more info on that here - https://www.axios.com/small-businesses-lost-coronavirus-recession-minorities-22a03253-156f-4397-829d-067940d00300.html This is absolutely heartbreaking. https://theohiostar.com/2020/06/11/coronavirus-restrictions-devastate-black-business-owners-who-are-down-41-percent-study/

column31: Love—Just What the Doctor Ordered for A Powerful Immune System Love comes in many shapes and sizes. No matter where you stand on the subject, one thing is becoming clearer. Strong relationships and love are good for your health. Here are a few of the possible health benefits of love: • Less frequent trips to the doctor: Studies have linked marriage to fewer doctor visits and shorter hospital stays. It’s thought that people in good relationships are more likely to take better care of themselves. • Reduced risk of depression and substance abuse: Although it shouldn’t be surprising, people in good marriages have lower rates of depression, drinking, and drug abuse. • Less anxiety: According to a study using MRI brain scans, strongly connected couples in long-term relationships have more activation in the areas of the brain associated with bonding and less in the area that produces anxiety.1 • Healthier blood pressure: A good relationship can be good for your blood pressure. A study in the Annals of Behavioral Medicine showed that happily married people had better blood pressure than singles. The worst were unhappily married people.2 • Better stress management: Research has shown a link between good social support and relationships and improved ability to cope with stress. • Healthier immune system: People in healthy relationships are less likely to get sick after exposure to cold or flu viruses. This may be partly due to reduced stress and depression resulting in enhanced immune response.3 • Longer lifespan: Many research studies have linked happy marriages to longer life. The feeling of love and connection helps protect against loneliness and isolation, which are tied to increased mortality risk. • Happier life: One of the greatest benefits of love is joy. According to research in the Journal of Family Psychology, happiness depends more on the quality of family relationships than on the level of income.4 You don’t have to be married or in love to have good health and live a long life. But reduced stress, lower levels of anxiety, and strong social connections are key ingredients in a recipe for a longer, healthier life. Viruses tend to adjust to their host species by becoming less virulent over time.  This happened with SARS and happening now with COVID-19, researchers from Arizona State University find. 

"During the middle and late phases of the SARS epidemic, SARS-CoV accumulated mutations that attenuated the virus. Scientists believe that a weakened virus that causes less severe disease may have a selective advantage if it is able to spread efficiently through populations by people who are infected unknowingly."

column31: Genetically. Modified. Mosquitoes. A company called Oxitec has received an experimental use permit from the US EPA, to release genetically modified mosquitos into the wild. The permit would allow for the release of millions of genetically modified mosquitos each week over the next TWO YEARS. They hope that these genetically modified mosquitos can help eliminate diseases that are typically carried by mosquitos. The plan is that genetically modified male mosquitos will mate with wild females, and their genetics will cause the children to die, and should cause a collapse of the wild population. They will be released in Florida and Texas, and easily be able to travel throughout the country from there. This was tried before in Florida in 2016, but was cancelled after local residents complained about the potential dangers. A public forum for the recent permit application showed 31,174 comments opposing the release of the mosquitos and only 56 in support. The EPA promised to consider these votes during their review process. However, the permit still went through anyway. There is growing concern among scientists that this technology may not be ready for deployment, and that the risks have not been studied thoroughly enough. Many scientists are warning about the potential unintended consequences that can come from unleashing such insects into the wild. Researchers are unaware of what type of allergic reactions that these insects could cause if they interact with people... What are your thoughts? https://anewspost.com/genetically-modified-mosquitoes-cleared-for-release-in-the-us/

column31: Ringworm is not a worm but actually a fungus. It gets its name from the common ring it makes on the skin. It is highly contagious and can easily spread from touch to others or to another part of your body. Though commonly found in children it can also be found in adults and pets. Symptoms can be bothersome but often can be easily fixed naturally with things you likely have one hand. Symptoms: -Red ring -Blisters -Inflammation -Itchiness -Crust covering the site -Scaly to touch Ring worm is passed by: -Person to person (Touching someone else who has it) -Person to self (Spreading it over your own body) -Thing to person (Ex. Using the same towel as someone who has it) -Animal to person (Ex. Dog having it) -Soil to person (Getting it from the soil) Ringworm is fungal – so can be treated anti-fungal means. Luckily there are many natural anti-fungal’s out there. A few are: Tea Tree Oil – This always makes my must have list and this is one reason why – it’s anti-fungal. Mix it with some coconut oil to make a paste and apply to the area. No-More-Yeast – Has anti-fungal oils that are effective in treating rashes and skin irritations, including ringworm. Aloe Vera – Though this will not get rid of the fungus aloe helps with the irritation of the skin from the rash. Licorice root – This anti-fungal is commonly effective in treating skin irritations, including ringworm. Mix 5 table spoons in boiling water and let simmer. Apply to the affected area a few times a day. Ginger tea – Ginger tea has so many wonderful uses – including this. You can drink the tea or make a compress and place it on the site. Raw garlic paste –This is likely the most easy and most common for everyone to have on hand. Garlic has anti-fungal properties. Blend up about 6 teaspoons to make a paste. You can apply up to three times a day with a Q-tip or cotton ball. ** It is crucial to continue treatment for a week or two after the symptoms have cleared in order to prevent re-occurrence.

column31: "Dismantle the police" However, when you need help and need to call 911, who are you going to call - ghostbusters?! "Calling MPLS Cops is ....Privilege?!" "Defund and dismantle the police department". Do folks have any idea what society would look like without law and order!? Can you imagine a world in which 911 wasnt an option, in which people had free reign to run amuck and commit any crime they fancied, a vigilante system of gun fights on lawless streets!? 👮‍♂️🤦‍♂️🤔 Burn down the cities and then allow some Antifa Appointed Community Action Committee to patrol the streets. 9 of 12 City Council Members violated Minnesota's 'Open Meeting Law' by appearing together at a rally and discussing official policy to end the Police Dept. The President of the Minneapolis City Council appeared on CNN claiming the ability to call the police when you are in danger comes from "a place of privilege." CAMEROTA: "What if in the middle of the night my home is broken into. Who do I call?" BENDER: "Yes, I hear that loud and clear from a lot of my neighbors. And I know — and myself, too, and I know that that comes from a place of privilege." Council member Jeremiah Ellison promised that the council would “dismantle” the department. (H/T Frank Pafko) FOX9 reported that the Minneapolis City Council’s plan to dismantle the Police Department could run into a little snag called the City Charter. Since that time the Minneapolis City Charter webpage is returning an error message. Likely, from all the media trying to find out why their reporting has been wrong. Directly from the City Charter: City Charter - Departments 7.2. a. The departments generally. The City Council must establish, organize, and otherwise provide for these departments The Charter also specifies funding and force levels. c. Funding. The City Council must fund a police force of at least 0.0017 employees per resident, and provide for those employees' compensation, for which purpose it may tax the taxable property in the City up to 0.3 percent of its value annually. This tax is in addition to any other tax, and not subject to the maximum set under section 9.3(a)(4) * Excerpts from Mr. Pafko It sure looks like the radicals on the Minneapolis City Council forgot to research exactly what power they have to effect change. The media also made a big mistake, they believed what they were told. The City Charter can be amended. However, that requires a proposal from the City Charter Commission, not the Council. It can be approved by either of two ways: 1. By ballot question - An amendment submitted to the electorate must be approved by an affirmative majority vote of those voting on the question for it to be enacted. 2. By ordinance - An amendment may be enacted by ordinance if passed by the unanimous affirmative vote of the entire membership of the City Council and the approval of the mayor. So, based solely on this supposed “veto-proof vote”, the Minneapolis City Council can’t dismantle the Police Department and can’t defund the Police Department without an amendment to the City Charter. This is all planned out by the elites and their leftist globalistic ideology tactics to destabilize the world. They want it to be like the Wild Wild West people! The more upheavel - the better for them.

column31: So many "systems" are broken in America. The medical system, the education system, the justice system.... And we see so many people who are bullied and broken by these systems. It doesn't matter that "not all" people who are part of these systems are that way, or that many don't intend to cause harm. THE SYSTEMS are broken. They allow and encourage this bullying, the taking of peoples' rights, the harshness with which they are treated. And we want to see reform across the board. These systems are full of corruption. Lets look at the medical system. Doctors aren't taught about nutrition. They aren't taught the benefits of being in nature, breathing fresh air, and getting sunlight. The medical profession is bought by the pharmaceutical industry, not only in terms of the practice of medicine, but also teaching and research. It is one giant business. We can specifically see this corruption in these scary stats.... *Maternal mortality went from 7.2 per 100,000 in 1987 to nearly 30 per 100,000 in 2019! (White mothers are 26 per 100k, while Black mothers are nearly 64 per 100k) *250,000 die annually from medical mistakes These numbers show that as doctors and pharmaceutical companies have intervened more, pushed drugs more heavily, and refused to address their system of paternalistic attitudes, we have had worse and worse outcomes (despite spending more than any developed nation on "health care"). And sadly, Black people have even worse outcomes than White people do. A widely used health care algorithm that helps determine which patients need additional attention was found to have a significant racial bias, favoring white patients over black ones who were sicker and had more chronic health conditions. “Your health care depends on who you are,” according to a 2014 report from the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation, the nation’s largest philanthropy dedicated to health. “Race and ethnicity continue to influence a patient’s chances of receiving many specific health care interventions and treatments.” This is unacceptable. Change needs to happen. We can start this change by taking our health into our own hands, and being prepared. By taking control of our health, the less we have to rely on the medical system! Change your diet. Eat more nutrient dense foods and drink plenty of water. Also make sure to add vitamins and herbal supplements to your daily routine. Make the switch to more natural body and hair products. Our bodies absorb what we put on them, so it's important to make sure we are using clean and safe products. Look into alternative providers if possible. Providers that take a more natural approach to healing. Community is also very important. Make sure you are surrounding yourself with like-minded people. People who will help support you on your journey to a more healthy lifestyle. It's our dream to increase access to people by partnering with local providers to open clinics inside of herbal shops. We can't wait until natural options are as common as pharmacies! We want Freedom right? We want Equality right? Level the playing field: Vaccination is NOT one size fits all. Protect our Black Community from vaccine injuries. #blacklivesmatter #BLM STUDIES: The study “Racial Differences in Pediatric Food Allergy” (2019) found that "When compared with Caucasian children, African-American (odds ratio [OR], 2.34) and Hispanic (OR, 2.88) children had significantly higher rates of food-induced anaphylaxis.” - Another study "RACIAL DIFFERENCES IN FOOD ALLERGY PHENOTYPE AND HEALTH CARE UTILIZATION AMONG US CHILDREN”(2016) finds "Compared with non-Hispanic White children, AA children had significantly higher rates of having asthma and eczema, and significantly higher rates of allergy to wheat, soy, corn, fish and shellfish.” - African American women were 20 percent more likely to have asthma than non-Hispanic whites, in 2015. - In 2015, African American children had a death rate ten times that of non-Hispanic white children. - Black children are 4 times more likely to be admitted to the hospital for asthma, as compared to non-Hispanic white children. - Autism diagnoses are for the first time higher in black children than caucasian children, who historically had higher rates. column31: Guys, what is learned helplessness? "A condition in which a person suffers from a sense of powerlessness, arising from a traumatic event or persistent failure to succeed. It is thought to be one of the underlying causes of depression." It's now come into the mindset of adults, children, and professionals. "The concept of learned helplessness was discovered accidentally by psychologists Martin Seligman and Steven F. Maier. They had initially observed helpless behavior in dogs that were classically conditioned to expect an electrical shock after hearing a tone." Some common symptoms of learned helplessness include: ⚠️ Low self-esteem ⚠️ Passivity ⚠️ Poor motivation ⚠️ Giving up ⚠️ Lack of effort ⚠️ Frustration ⚠️ Procrastination ⚠️ Not researching on your own ⚠️ Failure to ask for help ⚠️ Repeating what main stream media says ⚠️ Not learning to take charge of your own body, health and life ⚠️ Staying glued to "authority and experts" on how to proceed and live Problem ➜ Reaction ➜ Solution. column31: “Please send someone over. We’re all getting sick. I have diabetes. My wife has asthma....” This Maasai warrior, Dickson Gisa (far left), contacted the Weston A. Price Foundation (WAPF) with these words. He had heard about the physical degeneration that comes w/ abandoning tradl. diets & it had resonated w/ his own experience & that of his community in his village Oiti, in Kenya near the border of Tanzania. WAPF sent me in June 2015. (I was one of the first volunteers to raise my hand to go. 😊) Dickson & I spoke before my trip.“You teach & you learn,” he said to me. What joy for me to do just that! I learned MUCH—such as making yogurt in gourds & eating fresh organ meats, community decision-making and more. And I also had the privilege of communicating what I understood about the importance of traditional diets & culture. To my surprise, the night before we left the village, Dickson clothed us in traditional Maasai clothing as a gift. 😍🙏 It was humbling & beautiful 🧡 to be invited 🧡 to be welcomed 🧡 to be taught 🧡 to be heard 🧡 to be embraced This exchange shaped the trajectory of my life’s mission & vision. I want to continue to connect with, learn from, and THANK people the globe over for their wisdom. 🌍 Check out Wise Traditions podcast #29 to hear his story in his own words—including his childhood dietary habits, the allure of “foreign foods” and the corresponding rise in the incidences of cancer, diabetes, and other diseases heretofore unknown by his village. @ Kenya

column31: Aware friends, today, let's talk the Immune System and Molds. Many clients will scan for molds and/or have symptoms of mold toxitity and perhaps not even know the connection. Having these assessed and cleared by a skilled root cause practitioner will be important for short and long terms healing. Our immune systems protect us from dangerous pathogens, like bacteria, including Lyme’s Borrelia burgdorferi, parasites, viruses, and fungi (including mold). It shields us from the harmful substances we encounter, including environmental toxins, heavy metals, biotoxins, and more. White blood cells, called lymphocytes, carry out adaptive immune responses. There are two broad classes of these responses: cell-mediated immune responses and antibody responses. They are carried out by different types of lymphocytes, called T cells and B cells, respectively. In the cell-mediated immune response, activated T cells take direct action against foreign antigens. T cells might kill an infected or toxic host cell. Or, the T cell might produce a signal molecule that activates macrophages which engulf and destroy invaders, toxins, and cellular debris. Activated B cells secrete antibodies–proteins called immunoglobulins. The antibodies circulate in the system, where they bind specifically to the foreign antigens, inactivating the mold biotoxins. As a result, the biotoxins can no longer bind to receptors on host cells. Mycotoxin exposure comes from ingestion, dermal transmission, and inhalation. Mold toxins are extremely potent and often affect nearly every organ system in the body. Some of the symptoms associated with Chronic Inflammatory Response Syndrome (CIRS) include: +Brain fog, memory issues, cognitive and focus difficulties +Mood swings +Digestive problems +Fatigue; weakness +Frequent urination; excessive thirst; dehydration +Weight gain +Muscle and joint pain +Blurry vision; light sensitivity +Postnasal drip; sore throat +Numbness; tingling +Tinnitus +Static shocks +Dizziness +Metallic taste in the mouth +Low-grade fever +Shortness of breath +Headache Key elements of the immune system which I bioscan assess for clients include: 📈 +Spleen Your spleen helps your body fight infection. Just as it quality checks red blood cells, your spleen can identify unwelcome pathogens in your blood. In conjunction with the lymph nodes, it creates an organized force of defender cells called lymphocytes. Lymphocytes are specific white blood cells that produce antibodies. +Lymph Nodes These are nodes, vessels, and tissues located throughout the body, including in the neck, armpits, abdomen, and groin. The lymph nodes help break down harmful germs. Also, they filter toxins for removal from the body in lymph fluid. White blood cells contained in the lymph nodes help fight infection. +Bone Marrow Bone marrow is the spongy tissue located inside some of the bones in the body, such as the hip and thigh bones. Bone marrow makes 200 billion new red blood cells every day.3 It also produces white blood cells and platelets. If the bone marrow isn’t functioning well and produces abnormal white blood cells, those cells may be unable to fight infection. +White Blood Cells The bone marrow produces white blood cells, or leukocytes. These are crucial for a healthy immune system. They fight and protect against infections. They are stored in the spleen, the bone marrow, and the lymph nodes. White blood cells can circulate throughout the body. They collect in areas where there is an infection. +Mycotoxins can significantly impair the antibody production of the adaptive immune system. They can reduce the growth and spread of lymphocytes. 🍃 Since I am solution focused, here is a thorough article on how to handle mold deeply ➜ http://www.integrativenutritionaltherapies.com/conquering-candida-and-fungal-infections-permanently/ 🦠Also, here is a powerful supportive mold kit I highly recommend ➜ https://bit.ly/2PahnOo:=:https://microbeformulas.com/collections/all-products/products/mold-kit?rfsn=2166149.336e38&utm_source=refersion&utm_medium=affiliate&utm_campaign=2166149.336e38
column34: MYCOTOXINS Molds produce toxic compounds called mycotoxins. These compounds are also known as biotoxins since they are poisonous substances produced by living organisms. Mold toxicity occurs when mycotoxins affect a body adversely, leading to chronic symptoms. SOME COMMON TYPES OF MYCOTOXINS INCLUDE: Aflatoxins Ochratoxins Trichothecenes NOTE: Mycotoxins are considered carcinogenic and and potentially deadly.

column31: The top 10 lies from the "healthcare" system Lie #1) Pharmaceuticals prevent disease The big push by Big Pharma is now focused on treating healthy people with drugs as if pharmaceuticals were nutrients that could somehow prevent disease. But pharmaceuticals don’t prevent disease, and medications are not vitamins. Lie #2) Doctors are experts in health Doctors don’t even study health...they study disease. Modern doctors are taught virtually nothing about nutrition, wellness or disease prevention. Lie #3) You have no role in your own healing Doctors, drug companies and health authorities all want you to believe that your health is determined by their interventions. If you believe them, you have virtually no role in your own health or healing...it’s all managed by their drugs, their screening, their surgeries and their interventions. Lie #4) Disease is a matter of bad luck or bad genes Western medicine wants you to believe in the mythology of spontaneous disease...disease that strikes without cause. This is equivalent to saying that disease is some sort of voodoo black magic and that patients have no way to prevent disease through their own diets or lifestyle choices. Western medicine claims to be driven by scientific, rational thinking, and yet the entire industry still fails to acknowledge that chronic disease always has a cause and that most of the time, that cause has everything to do with nutritional deficiencies, exposure to toxic chemicals and a lack of exercise. Lie #5) Vaccines are safe and effective Vaccines have emerged as the greatest and most insidious mythology yet fabricated by western medicine. They have been proven to do more harm than good. Lie #6) Screening equals prevention Western medicine doesn’t believe in disease prevention. Rather, the industry believes in screening while calling it prevention. But screening isn’t prevention by even the wildest stretch of the imagination. In fact, virtually all the popular screening methodologies actually promote diseases. Mammography, for example, emits so much radiation that it causes breast cancer in tens of thousands of women each year. Imaging dyes used in radiological scans can cause horrific side effects, and psychiatric “disorder” screening is little more than a thinly-disguised patient recruitment scheme disguised as medicine. Lie #7) Health insurance will keep you healthy The lie supposes that merely having health insurance will provide some sort of magical protection against disease. But in reality, health insurance doesn’t make you healthy! It is only YOU and your choices about foods, exposures to toxic chemicals, pursuit of exercise and time in nature that can make you healthy. Health insurance is, in effect, a wager that you will get sick. How does gambling on your sickness provide any protection whatsoever for your health? It doesn’t. Lie #8) Hospitals are places of health and healing If you want to stay healthy or get healthy, a hospital is the very last place you want to find yourself. They are unhappy and unhealthy places. Hospitals usually serve disease-promoting foods and lack health-enhancing sunlight, and potentially deadly mistakes with pharmaceuticals or surgical procedures now appear to be frighteningly common in U.S. hospitals. Lie #9) Conventional medicine is “advanced” state-of-the-art medicine Even though doctors and health authorities try to pass off western medicine as being “advanced” or “modern,” the whole system is actually pathetically outdated and stuck in the germ theory of disease. Western medicine has yet to even acknowledge the role of nutrition in preventing disease. Western medicine fails to acknowledge mind-body medicine and believes the mind plays virtually no role in healing. Lie #10) More research is needed to find “cures” This lie is especially ridiculous because western medicine does not believe in any “cure” for any disease. They aren’t even looking for cures! This lie has been repeated since the 1960’s, when cancer scientists claimed they were only a few years away from curing cancer. Today, four decades later, can you think of a single major disease that western medicine has cured? There aren’t any. That’s because drug companies make money from sick people, not cured people. A patient cured is a patient lost. It is far more profitable to keep patients sick and pretend to “manage” their disease through a lifetime of pharmaceuticals. So when drug companies and disease non-profits claim to be searching for a “cure,” what they’re really doing is taking your money to fund more drug research to patent more medications that don’t actually cure anything. Remember this the next time you’re asked to donate to some search for “the cure.” The cures already exist in nutrition, herbal remedies and naturopathic medicine, but Big Pharma and the conventional medicine cartel isn’t interested in real cures they only want to promote the idea of (truncated)
